# 4. EXPOSE

## What is EXPOSE?

EXPOSE informs Docker and other developers which port the application inside the container is expected to listen on.

Syntax:

```dockerfile
EXPOSE 8080
```

Example:

```dockerfile
EXPOSE 5000
```

Important:

EXPOSE does NOT publish or open the port.

It only documents the intended port.

Actual port publishing is done using:

```bash
docker run -p 8080:8080 image_name
```

(Will be learned later.)

